  "base_url": "https://www.virustotal.com/api/v3/",
  "documentation_url": "https://docs.virustotal.com/reference/overview",
  "setup_instructions": "## Get a VirusTotal API key\n\nVirusTotal API access uses a per-account **API key**. The free public key is rate-limited (4 requests/min, 500/day); paid Premium keys lift the limits and unlock private scans.\n\n### 1. Create / sign in to a VirusTotal account\n1. Open https://www.virustotal.com/ and click **Sign in** (top right).\n2. Register with email, Google, or Microsoft. Verify your email if prompted.\n\n### 2. Copy the API key\n1. Click your avatar in the top right → **API Key**.\n2. Copy the long alphanumeric string shown under **Your API key**.\n\n### 3. Paste the key below\nPaste it in the **API Key** field. T1 sends it as the `x-apikey` request header automatically — no prefix needed.\n\nClick **Test Authentication** to confirm. The test calls `/users/<your-key>` and expects a 200.\n\n### Rate limits to know about\n- **Free tier**: 4 requests/minute, 500/day, 15.5K/month. T1 will surface a `QuotaExceededError` when you hit these — investigations may stall briefly during bursts.\n- **Premium**: agreed limits per contract (typically 1,000+/min) and access to `intelligence/`, `private/`, and live hunting endpoints.\n\n### Troubleshooting\n- **`401 Wrong API key`**: Key was rotated, deleted, or copied with whitespace. Re-copy from the VT account page.\n- **`429 Quota exceeded`**: You're past the per-minute or per-day limit. Wait, or upgrade to Premium.\n- **`403 Forbidden`** on `intelligence/` or `private/` endpoints: free keys cannot access these — Premium only.",
  "actions": [
